cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.LG. 

This paper deals with the axiomatization and complexity of a modal logic with a "knowing what" operator, which is a topic that falls under the scope of logic and knowledge representation. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Additionally, the paper discusses the decidability and complexity of the logic, which suggests that it could also be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The use of Kripke models and tableaux also indicates a connection to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
